snippet.textDisplay:
For Post-Mortem!

1. Where was Carmen sleeping the night of Todd’s supposed death? The apartment that she shared with her husband above Todd’s cafe, or the house that’s 500 yards uphill?

2. What was the reason for the vague time of Todd arriving back to the cafe after the party (3am - 4:20am)? Was the driver’s testimonial suspicious?

3. Was the autopsy surgeon also the coroner? My understanding is that the autopsy report seems genuine along with Mrs. Ford’s claim that she was on the phone with Todd... therefore I would suspect the coroner pegging the time of death at Sunday 5am Sunday might be doubtful

P.S. Thanks for making Saturdays something to look forward to!

Daniel and Steph

snippet.textDisplay:
Just a thought. They should have tried to look into people who holds a grudge against Roland West. Seeing as Todd was left in his garage, and the theory that he killed her isn't exactly solid, the most probable explanation is that she was left there as a message for him perhaps because getting to her was easier than getting to his wife. Maybe the people who harmed her only wanted to injure her, and her death was indeed an accident due to the fact that the people who put her there might not be very knowledgeable of carbon monoxide poisoning. That would also explain why West said in his death bed that he was responsible for Todd's death.

#Postmortem

This is what I think may have happened:
Todd was coming home, she probably left something in her car and decided to go and look for it, maybe a mugger found that the garage door was open. She left her car maybe thinking it was her husband but she was sadly mistaken. He may have had a blunt object but tried to knock her out before she could think of running, hence her broken noes. That didn't stop her and she quickly realized she was endanger and tried to run. This person may have then used the blunt object to take her down. It worked and she collapsed. Just like what shane said "hair back then was pretty firm" due to the products and such. He couldn't find any money or rich jewelry so he left it alone. The mugger probably wouldn't have wanted her to say alive since she might have seen his face so Todd who can barely move was placed into the car and the mugger jammed the key into the car so that it wouldn't come out no matter how hard Todd tried to take it out. He wanted it to look like a drunken accident so that's why he didn't finish her off, he didn't want to many clues left behind. He ran away, closing the door behind him and Todd sat their in her car, and possibly passed out from the immense pain of her broken bones. Where she then died.

So for the postmortem:
I would highly suggest it was pat dicicco, i simply attribute him to the case because i wanted to think of an overall conclusive storyline that fit with what the coroner said of the body. The coroner could easily have been threated by dicicco to not give "too much" information thereforehe requested others look into it to take the heat off himself. The peas and carrots could be explained by dicicco taking her out to a nice fancy lunch, in which she ate the smaller section of the meal (as most of us do after a night of heavy drinking) working around things like steak,potatoes ,or anything else that would be culturally appropriate to serve with peas and carrots. I also offer the suggestion that ,since the coroner didn't give very conclusive evidence besides the monoxide poisoning, dicicco punched out the starlet breaking her nose. I would then say he stuffed her into the trunk of his car (probably small trunk) breaking her ribs unintentionally. Being a former lover dicicco wouldn't think to go through her purse to remove the key cause he wouldn't figure she had one to wests place. He would start the car to finish her off thus blaming it on west. #postmortem #Ibelieveinspiritsbutnotlikeryan
